Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.86,0:00:02.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's almost the tenth anniversary of Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.42,0:00:04.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We made it through the first,\Nnow let's aim for the next!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.61,0:00:06.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The climax of the {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.25,0:00:09.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An unexpected comment from Ran leads to a deduction we overlooked!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.95,0:00:11.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.45,0:00:13.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:15.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.25,0:01:54.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A rich family with a mansion in Shizuoka called us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.65,0:01:58.11,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In that mansion, for the past several years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.11,0:02:01.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a series of events took place, always on a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day, on the 4th of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:05.26,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then on the October 4 {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.67,0:02:08.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}there were two victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found fingerprints on the rope and the medicine bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.09,0:02:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well? Whose prints did they find?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.42,0:02:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.43,0:02:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-They don't belong to anyone who works here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, now we know this was an outside job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.14,0:02:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we go back to our rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.60,0:02:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm going to have to station officers in front of your doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.50,0:02:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{o-yasumi kudasai}Rest well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.97,0:02:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.65,0:02:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} live?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:56.05,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kenzo Akatsuka (50)\NKunitomo Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.53,0:02:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, his company is in...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.13,0:02:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.76,0:03:00.09,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masashi Watabiki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chauffeur
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.39,0:02:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sekiguchi Security. It's in Yokohama, Nishi Ward, the Umeda neighborhood!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.62,0:03:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're very informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.86,0:03:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pick him up at his place whenever he visits here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.63,0:03:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this guy takes notes on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.44,0:03:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know someone in Yokohama...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.85,0:03:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.00,0:03:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you bugging me at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.99,0:03:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshimichi Sekiguchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, I met him a couple of times when I was a rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.05,0:03:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember him 'cause he got on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.33,0:03:30.50,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What do you want from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.79,0:03:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was found hanged here in Shizuoka, at the home of a man named Kunitomo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.02,0:03:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he hanged himself, it's suicide, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.16,0:03:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.06,0:03:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master of the house was killed shortly afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I met him for questioning while we were searching
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for the president of his security company...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Searching?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.85,0:03:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president of the company went missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.56,0:04:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been 13 years and he still hasn't been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Thirteen years?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, he vanished around the end of September.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was on Mom's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.93,0:04:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president of the company disappeared on September 26, 13 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.67,0:04:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kunitomo's cruiser sank off the coast of Suruga Bay that year on September 29!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:24.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Three days before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.94,0:04:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Sekiguchi guy took over as president of the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanna go out for drinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.52,0:04:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup! As long as you're paying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh... Buy your men a drink now and then!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.92,0:04:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're such a miser!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call me frugal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.76,0:04:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:43.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A miser...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.56,0:04:46.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All the suspects have strange habits and phobias.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You three should get some rest, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.96,0:04:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't we look around the suspects' rooms before we go to bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.53,0:05:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's find out if their funny hang-ups are real!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why I'm afraid of sharp objects?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.95,0:05:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was a little girl, I was trying to grab my mother's sewing kit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:12.27,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shigeko Senzaki (52)\NKunitomo Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:12.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I fell and stabbed myself in the forehead with a needle!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That had to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.67,0:05:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!{arere}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.59,0:05:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that why you taped that calendar to the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.31,0:05:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are marks on the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.85,0:05:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, those are our birthdays. Me, my daughter Namika, Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.00,0:05:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s father and Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who died in the accident on the ship,\Nwere all childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We used to throw a big birthday party for the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twenty years ago, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother died from an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.75,0:05:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There used to be eight birthdays on this calendar, but now we're down to four...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm acrophobic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're better off asking Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.09,0:06:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you fall from a high place because of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.77,0:06:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they {\i1}saved{\i0} me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:07.24,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Namika Senzaki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chef
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.20,0:06:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was in fourth grade,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I fell out of a tree in the garden, and Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, his left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd forgotten all about it until I saw the scar on his left hand a couple of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.60,0:06:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He nearly always wears gloves because of his fear of germs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.51,0:06:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My memory's so fuzzy. Before I saw the scar, I always thought it was his brother who saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.19,0:06:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your room's very clean, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.13,0:06:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chef has to keep everything hygienic!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.49,0:06:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.57,0:06:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't poke around in a lady's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.86,0:06:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's the scar from that injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.27,0:06:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.45,0:06:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You even wear gloves in your room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.53,0:06:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.55,0:06:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only take them off to sleep, bathe and touch the fingerprint reader upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait... I also take them off when I drive or use a pen because the gloves slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, this must be the baseball glove your brother used!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.67,0:07:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only when he was a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's your baseball glove?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike my brother, I've never been much of an athlete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your calendar has a lot of notes on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.42,0:07:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I once forgot an important errand for the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since then, I've kept notes on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why am I a perfectionist?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.09,0:07:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do I need a reason to be neat and tidy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.55,0:07:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little extreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.95,0:07:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems true that you're very well-organized, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.07,0:07:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything in your room is perfectly straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel uncomfortable otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there anybody here who's the opposite of you? Really sloppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think "sloppy" is the right term to use,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.90,0:07:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} can be a bit like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.40,0:08:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a time when the plates she stacked in the cupboard were 3 mm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} always stack them perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?{arere}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.40,0:08:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this your compass?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.43,0:08:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I like to go hiking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, did you notice the letters carved on the dial plate of Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did. E and N, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.12,0:08:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.50,0:08:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were like this compass,\Nthe N and E would be switched.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.84,0:08:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How should I know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.39,0:08:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we've checked out\Nthe rooms of all four suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.55,0:08:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but we didn't find anything, did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.27,0:08:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope! The kid wasted our time again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.99,0:08:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's continue the investigation after we get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.36,0:08:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.73,0:08:47.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is it? There's something bugging me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.03,0:08:49.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something I've overlooked...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.10,0:08:52.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something that's not right... but {\i1}what{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.24,0:08:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.96,0:08:57.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought you a new pair of jammies!\NWant to wear them tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.13,0:08:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be twinsies again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.73,0:09:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twinsies?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.53,0:09:04.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.90,0:09:07.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I never considered that possibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.57,0:09:09.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And if that's the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.35,0:09:12.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the unusual way Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.22,0:09:15.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the way the murderer got past the fingerprint authentication system...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.46,0:09:17.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the murderer's ability to disappear from the third floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.71,0:09:20.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and the reason Kunitomo was frightened to death
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.49,0:09:21.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}can all be explained!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.90,0:09:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, nice work!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.26,0:09:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.46,0:09:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogoro asked me to call the four suspects and the mistress to the third floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s figured out who the murderer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.04,0:09:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh! I think he has!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.90,0:09:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's someone in this house,\Nso he wants you to keep an eye out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.28,0:09:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he's going to start his deduction show now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.84,0:09:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he said he'll start in three hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Three hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.87,0:09:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only if you follow the instructions I'm about to give you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.33,0:09:57.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.21,0:10:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd you wake us up at the crack of dawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.66,0:10:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.26,0:10:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called you here to reveal the truth about the two murders that just occurred here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.06,0:10:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.85,0:10:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the murderer is among you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the first murder, Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged from the balcony of this bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought we were all cleared because of the time of death and the details of the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.75,0:10:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has acrophobia,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.17,0:10:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so she couldn't have hanged somebody from a balcony on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.11,0:10:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is afraid of sharp objects,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so she would've avoided hanging the body over that iron fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.27,0:10:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The message printed on the card planted on Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} by the murderer was crooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's something an obsessive-compulsive like Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would never do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.26,0:10:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was driving the master and his wife to the hospital at the time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.76,0:10:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so they couldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.61,0:10:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.86,0:11:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you going to accuse one of us of faking our mental condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.26,0:11:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room was very clean, but there was dust on the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.74,0:11:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really {\i1}are{\i0} unable to get close to windows, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.75,0:11:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had no sharp objects in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.25,0:11:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even her calendar was held up with tape instead of thumbtacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Akatsuka's room was impeccable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.13,0:11:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's safe to say none of you are lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's look into the {\i1}second{\i0} murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.32,0:11:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow the murderer managed to get past the fingerprint authentication to enter the bedroom on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.93,0:11:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This person appeared before the master, inducing a heart attack, crushed his heart pills...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then disappeared from the room without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One possibility is that he or she hid somewhere on the third floor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.90,0:11:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after seeing Conan climb up the escape rope...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:12:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and hid among us when we all crowded into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.06,0:12:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you found fingerprints on the rope and medicine bottle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suspect they belong to the {\i1}accomplice{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-An accomplice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, there are {\i1}two{\i0} murderers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.57,0:12:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying one of us let the mystery person in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.29,0:12:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the master said he wouldn't see anyone until the day was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.19,0:12:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we looked all over the third floor after the crime, but we didn't find anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I didn't see anyone go out into the hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,nor was there any sign of escape from a balcony or window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where is this accomplice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we asked you all here. So we can reenact the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we might have overlooked something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up, everybody! We're going to search one room at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.21,0:13:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unlike last time, I'll be the last person to enter the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.51,0:13:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to keep my eye on each and every one of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.99,0:13:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you take on the job of entering the room first and searching the window and balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.15,0:13:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Start with the study next to the bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you see anything unusual, {\i1}report to me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't need to yell so loud! We can hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.31,0:13:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get carried away when I'm worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.44,0:13:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then. After you, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.28,0:13:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the window's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't see anybody out on the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we go in now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.52,0:13:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really think this will turn up something new?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.21,0:13:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.72,0:13:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then. On to the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Move on, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:13:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No suspicious people came out into the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.85,0:14:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh. We didn't find anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's all, I'd like to get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quiet! First, one question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.46,0:14:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}really{\i0} didn't see anybody new?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.91,0:14:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.55,0:14:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see anybody new or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.54,0:14:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-We didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there {\i1}was{\i0} an extra person in the rooms you just searched!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.64,0:14:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you listening? We didn't see anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there he is. One more person, right behind Inspector Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.51,0:14:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twins?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This is my younger brother, who works for the Kanagawa Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.49,0:14:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{doumo.}Howdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.68,0:14:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm heading home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.81,0:14:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell your boss I got involved in this investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.80,0:14:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.57,0:14:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:15:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer stood behind the rest of you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make sure they were the last to enter and leave each room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.67,0:15:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before reaching the room where the accomplice was hiding,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the murderer dropped back and stayed behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The accomplice joined the group when the others entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.05,0:15:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after Inspector Yokomizo had finished checking the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.49,0:15:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the accomplice was a twin wearing the same clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.21,0:15:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just like with Detective Yokomizo, nobody would notice they'd switched places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd look like the room had been empty from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.29,0:15:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.46,0:15:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one here has a tw—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.61,0:15:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started to catch on when Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} showed us her calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.95,0:15:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told us that 20 years ago she would circle the birthdays
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.66,0:15:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of herself, her husband and Namika...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.35,0:15:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, his brother and their parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Akatsuka and his wife. That's {\i1}nine{\i0} people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shigeko said there were {\i1}eight{\i0} birthdays, so maybe two of them shared a birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.63,0:16:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew for sure when Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us about falling out of a tree in fourth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.95,0:16:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wasn't sure which brother caught her...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they looked the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this murder was committed by you and your twin brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.59,0:16:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His brother died 13 years ago in the shipwreck!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.50,0:16:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he {\i1}didn't{\i0} die in that accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he survived and managed to swim ashore?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.20,0:16:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof, earlier, we saw a scar on Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.85,0:16:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the time he saved Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from falling out of that tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But earlier, when he borrowed Ran's pen, his hand had no scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.20,0:16:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And although the handwriting on Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s calendar looked roughly consistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the circles before each note were drawn differently from day to day!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suspect you switched places from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.24,0:16:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you took careful notes of everything in a single shared notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.30,0:17:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could pass as one person without raising any suspicions!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.57,0:17:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You waited for the opportunity to kill Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the master of the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.23,0:17:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First the younger brother drove the master and mistress to the hospital to create an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thirty minutes later, the elder brother, who had been hiding in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.90,0:17:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,used the fingerprint reader to ring for Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to open the door for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once inside, he strangled Sekiguchi and hanged him from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few hours later, he entered the third floor again and killed the master by giving him a heart attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.07,0:17:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the master had refused to see anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.50,0:17:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} agreed to let Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in because he'd been with the master when the murder took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.10,0:17:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had no reason not to trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the master got the shock of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when two identical men walked into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.04,0:17:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one of them had been dead for 13 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.08,0:18:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The younger brother deliberately left his fingerprints on the medicine bottle and rope
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like the work of a stranger,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.71,0:18:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,completely clearing the household staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.21,0:18:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We never found anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.67,0:18:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I told Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to check the windows...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and why I shouted at you when I gave you orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.59,0:18:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the accomplice, hiding somewhere on the third floor, would also hear me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.98,0:18:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and know it was safe to hide on the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.36,0:18:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This house is surrounded by officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go in and get your brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you confess to the murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.39,0:18:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.13,0:18:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! If you're alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.30,0:18:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.60,0:18:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.55,0:18:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.68,0:18:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they were left to drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.67,0:18:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on? What {\i1}really{\i0} happened all those years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we got out to sea, the ship started having problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.26,0:19:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dove into the water to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person's bag was entangled in the screw propeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I saw an arm sticking out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably the president of Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s company, who went missing 13 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.90,0:19:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} talked his way onto the cruise so he could dispose of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.66,0:19:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the "fifth soul" mentioned on the first card.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you and your husband know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I didn't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.25,0:19:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I had warned everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.87,0:19:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sekiguchi suddenly shoved my father away from the wheel and sped the ship up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:48.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have been trying to get the bag off the propeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.69,0:19:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead, he capsized the ship, throwing everyone into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.49,0:19:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only life raft bobbed up right in front of Sekiguchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.70,0:19:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That piece of filth helped the master and mistress into the raft, then the three of them fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.17,0:19:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband and I were planning to come back with help!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.22,0:20:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:06.05,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:10.21,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We're all in this together now, so you'd better keep quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.55,0:20:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a while, we all managed to cling to a life preserver together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was clear we couldn't hold out for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.44,0:20:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had the most strength left, I volunteered to swim for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I lost consciousness before I reached the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.90,0:20:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I woke up, I was in a hospital bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.51,0:20:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with no memory of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.68,0:20:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran away from the hospital and started traveling Japan to figure out who I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.22,0:20:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, in the summer, I ran into my older brother by pure chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He helped me regain my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.53,0:20:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the day after that near-fatal car accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it was entirely my fault, the master kept apologizing to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my brother told me his story, I finally understood why.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.63,0:21:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it was just a coincidence that the master's nightmare and the car accident both happened on a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.76,0:21:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.83,0:21:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was our only hope of revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had no evidence to take to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.02,0:21:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we'd managed to find the sunken cruiser...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.31,0:21:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd never have found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.55,0:21:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sekiguchi lied to the police about where it sank.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.97,0:21:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real location was 34°45′ north, 138°30′ east.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.04,0:21:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The N and E carved on Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stands for north latitude 45 minutes, east longitude 30 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.58,0:21:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the cruiser sank somewhere in Suruga Bay, it's roughly 34° north and 138° east.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.40,0:21:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.39,0:21:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why use a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day on the 4th?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.88,0:21:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shipwreck happened on September 29, on a {\i1}taian{\i0} day!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,October 14, 13 years ago, was a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.19,0:22:03.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the day the master told the police to call off the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.93,0:23:32.87,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The cruiser had been moved by the tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.87,0:23:34.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the police managed to find it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.22,0:23:37.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}with the bag that caused all the trouble still entangled in the propeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.00,0:23:40.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Speaking of trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.31,0:23:42.72,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I was left with a crisis on my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.39,0:23:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Wear it just once so we can take a photo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.46,0:23:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.39,0:23:53.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You'll never get me in those pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:54.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seriously, pandas?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.66,0:24:01.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It just seemed like someone was watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.75,0:24:03.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was I imagining it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.91,0:24:06.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The window in the grenier...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.35,0:24:07.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A-A camera?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.39,0:24:09.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The detective office? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.50,0:24:12.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is it to get the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.00,0:24:13.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.91,0:24:14.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The men in...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.90,0:24:16.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Y-Yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.43,0:24:18.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yikes, yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:25.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.46,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.46,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Name Plate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.14,0:24:31.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, it's those two after a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.82,0:24:32.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.76,0:24:34.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You'll have to wait until next week to find out!
